	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
	
<div align="center">
<table BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td valign="top" align="left" nowrap>
		<strong><font face="Verdana" size="3">Leather Padding&nbsp;&nbsp;[<font color="yellow">Equipment</font>]</font></strong>
		&nbsp;&nbsp;<font face="Verdana" size="2"><a href="/ReportDocument.asp?ID=230701">[Report Bad Information]</a>
		</font>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign="top" align="left" nowrap>
		<font face="verdana" size="2">
		
		&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=230701"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
		</td>
	</tr>
	
  <tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
  
	<tr>
		<td valign="top" align="left">
		<font face="verdana" size="2"><b>Average Value:</b>&nbsp; 
		[7.45pp]&nbsp;(<a href="itemprices.asp?mode=details&amp;ID=230701">See Details</a>)
			&nbsp;(<a href="itemprices.asp?mode=new&amp;ID=230701">Submit Price</a>)
		</font>
		</td>
  </tr>
		

  
  <tr>
    <td valign="top" ><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div>
		
			<font face="verdana" size="2">
			<b>Stackable Item</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;
		<font face="verdana" size="2"><b>Weight:</b>&nbsp; </font><font face="verdana" size="2">0.1&nbsp;&nbsp;</font>
	
		
		
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td align="left">  
  	
	</td>
  </tr>
  <tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
  <tr>
    <td align="left" valign="top"><font face="Verdana" size="2">
    Used as a component to make Fine Steel Plate Armor, leather padding is made by combining a silk thread and a low quality skin or pelt in a sewing kit.  Leather padding becomes trivial at 31.  It has the appearance of a pelt in inventory, so be careful not to confuse it with one.  Any easy way to tell them apart is by the stacking number on the leather padding.</font>
    </td>
  </tr>
  
</table><br>
