			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I can't believe people charge 100+plat for a stack of this stuff.  It's too easy to make and the components are too easy to get.  For those of you searching for LQ skins to make this, get a smith to make you a skinning knife and then just skin your pelts down to LQ, takes no time at all and is a great way to pass the time if you're still low level.  All you do is put your MQ or HQ Pelts into your sewing kit with your Skinning Knife and click Combine.  Poof, you have a lower quality skin and your skill improves...I've never seen it fail either.  Personally, I've created characters specifically to get pelts and silk so I can make Leather Padding for my Smith.
				</font>
			</td>

