				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hey<BR>
I made leather padding with a tailoring skill of 1. I knew it was for fine plate and just fooled around to see if i could make it. I made it with no skill whatsoever on my first try. The given recepie is incorrect. FIRST you combine 2 spiderling silks to make a silk thread, THEN u combine a low quality pelt of any kind with your silk thread and &#161;poof!, leather padding at skill 1. and 4 all u people complaining about getting the spiderling silks, if u hunt in the east commons around inn 1, u can get about 20 of these in 8 minutes. At least, i can and im lvl 9. I think the low quality pelt is the hardest part of this recipe, being uncommon on pumas, bears, and plains cats, u usally get ruined, HQ or MQ, but rarely LQ.<BR>
